[
  {
    "type": "H1",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "How Expensive is Your Language"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "H1",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "I was inspired by the blog post "
      },
      {
        "data": {
          "openModal": true,
          "slatenode": {
            "href": "https://critter.blog/2021/01/29/use-the-smallest-word-that-does-the-job/"
          }
        },
        "type": "Link",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Use the smallest word that does the job"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": ", to explore to calculate how expensive one's writing is.  After some discussion with the author we agreed on a definition of expensive:"
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "The expense of a word is inversely related to the likelihood the audience knows it."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "The site "
      },
      {
        "data": {
          "openModal": true,
          "slatenode": {
            "href": "/www.wordfrequency.info"
          }
        },
        "type": "Link",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "www.wordfrequency.info"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " proves a list of the most commonly"
      },
      {
        "text": "1",
        "SuperScript": true
      },
      {
        "text": " used words I am using that as a proxy for cheap words and then having all other ones as expensive."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "If you want to see how expensive your writing is and you have an RSS feed enter it below.  We will compare it to some other feeds out there ("
      },
      {
        "text": "you can do multiple feeds one per line",
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": ")"
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Footnotes"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "1",
        "Bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": " I am using a list they provide that is all word forms of the 5000 most common words."
      }
    ]
  }
]
